Headquarters Regions: Greater New York Area, East Coast, Northeastern US
Full Description: There are many Futures Trading Platforms available today. Some of the Futures trading platforms are execution only and some come with Futures trading charts. Some of the cheaper or free Futures Trading Platforms only come with delayed quotes and are not real time.   Ideally you want to find a Futures Trading Platform that is free, comes with good execution, a good data feed, both fast and reliable and a good charting package. If you do find a good Free Platform, make sure you aren't over paying on the execution of the Futures and Commodity contracts to make up for the cost of the platform.  What to look for in a Futures Trading Platform:  * A reliable Futures Trading Platform  * A good Futures trading data feed  * Support for the Futures Trading Platform as long as the Futures markets are open.   * A Futures Trading Platform that can be customized to fit your trading style.  * The Futures Trading Platform needs to handle different types of orders, like OCO and Bracket orders as well as have stops and trailing stops.  * If you want to program trading strategies, does the platform give you a simple front end to set up Futures Trading strategies.

Description: Rapid data capture
Headquarters Regions: Greater Atlanta Area, East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: cd8a captures data through the commercial construction financing process. In every commercial construction project, subcontractors submit invoices to the General Contractor (GC). The GC creates their AIA G702 and G703 forms to be signed by an office of the company, the architect on the project, and a notary public. The GC submits this package of potentially hundreds of invoices to the developer in what's known as the "Application for Payment", or pay app. The developer adds in their soft costs (marketing, design, architecture, etc.), and submits that package to the lender, or in many cases, a loan service provider. From GC to developer to servicer to lender, every invoice is manually entered every month for every project.  There is no electronic sharing of data up this chain, so the financial analysis of the monthly progress of the project is done manually, which means manual data entry. cd8a removes the time - 2 to 10 hours per draw per month - associated with that manual data entry by applying crowdsourcing to complete the data entry in minutes, as opposed to hours or days it takes an analyst or accountant.  cd8a also securely stores all data electronically, making it a simple task to review past invoices or do discovery in the event of litigation.

Description: Access to health care varies across countries, groups, and individuals, largely influenced by social and economic
Headquarters Regions: Southern US
Full Description: Access to health care varies across countries, groups, and individuals, largely influenced by social and economic conditions as well as the health policies in place. Countries and jurisdictions have different policies and plans in relation to the personal and population-based health care goals within their societies. Health care systems are organizations established to meet the health needs of target populations. Their exact configuration varies between national and subnational entities. In some countries and jurisdictions, health care planning is distributed among market participants, whereas in others, planning occurs more centrally among governments or other coordinating bodies. In all cases, according to the World Health Organization (WHO), a well-functioning health care system requires a robust financing mechanism; a well-trained and adequately-paid workforce; reliable information on which to base decisions and policies; and well maintained health facilities and logistics to deliver quality medicines and technologies

Description: The Wide Limited Release Film Distribution Fund is seeking capital to scale-up regionally profitable films.
Headquarters Regions: Western US
Full Description: The Wide Limited Release Film Distribution Fund is seeking capital to scale-up regionally profitable films to reach a national audience, thus increasing their ROI exponentially. This is not a movie production company (but that is the closest category available among the industry choices Equity Net provides).  This is a fund to leverage the marketing of proven independent films and incorporates deals with the distributors.   Wide Limited Release will choose from  the best films that have already proven their dollar-in/dollar-out investment/profit function regionally and test them for national acceptance.  Those that test well will receive proper and appropriate capital to go national, increasing current profits from hundreds of thousands of dollars to tens of millions of dollars.  We have a slate of successful, profitable films that have only had limited release but shown exceptional ROI in those targeted areas.  The only thing holding them back from wide release and even bigger returns is capital. Wide Limited is looking for accredited investors who share its vision and is capable of providing seed money of $5,000,000.  However, Wide Limited will risk only $300,000  for initial tests before proceeding to the next level.   The funds will be used for advertising buys and earned media exposure to take proven profitable regional film distribution models, test them in other regions of the US, and then scale up to the national market for significant returns if tests prove successful.   Films are released either in a limited release (to a small targeted market) or a wide release (to the nation or world).   Appropriately capitalized, Wide Limited Release  will recoup every marketing dollar spent within six months and earn its profits from the DVD exploitation of such films in the next 18 months after theatrical release.  By duplicating this model repeatedly, it plans to provide its investors a minimum of 30% annual return on their money and a potential of 400%.

Description: More Nothing
Headquarters Regions: Great Lakes, Midwestern US
Full Description: The company that I’m raising money for (owned by my holding company Aisling Enterprises, LLC) is GreenSpace Enterprise Technologies.  GreenSpace is a hardware/software suite aimed at enterprise organizations looking to gain more insight into their facility utilization.  For example, Company A has facilities around the globe.  They currently send a person with a clipboard up to each floor 3 times a day to try to gauge how often rooms and desks are used, how many people are using the rooms and try to derive utilization rates from that information.  Obviously, this leaves much to be desired.  What about if someone just left the room?  Or, what if they just entered the room after the clipboard carrier just walked past?  How do we know if they used the projector or flat panel display?  They gain no insight into that information.  GreenSpace will allow them to see which rooms are used, when they are used, how many people are in the meeting (in the event 2 people are consistently holding down a 20 person conference room, etc.), and will allow them to shut down a projector or flat panel remotely in the event no one is in the room thereby saving energy and projector lamps.  The big seller is the ability to use the metrics on the back end.  Facility managers now have complete visibility as to how, when and where their space is used.  They can even see if the projectors and flat panels are being used.  There will be no more guessing as to how many meeting rooms are needed and what size they will need to be.  There will also be little debate as to whether or not they need more displays.  Once they have the utilization rates of all of that in front of them they’ll be able to make informed decisions.
